253 not use any alternative method including, but not limited to,
254 online portals, affiliated kiosks, or over-the-counter
255 transactions, to evade or exceed the limits provided for in
256 this section.
257 (n)(1) The commission, pursuant to Section 8-7A-19, may
258 assess a civil penalty against a person that violates this
259 section or a rule adopted or an order issued under this
260 section.
261 (2) Any proceeding under this section pursued by the
262 commission shall not preempt any criminal action or civil
263 liability which may arise under any other state law.
264 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
265 1, 2026.
